com.gliffy.restunit
Class Executor

java.lang.Object
  com.gliffy.restunit.Executor

public class Executor
extends Object

Handles the nuts and bolts of executing one call. This can be re-used, even if you wish to change HTTP implementations or comparators. This class's behavior can be configured in the following ways:

  • Http - this implements the basic HTTP protocol and allows you to use any implementation you wish. You must set something via setHttp(com.gliffy.restunit.http.Http).
  • ResultComparator - this performs the comparison of results. By default, this class uses the StrictMatchComparator. You may override this if custom comparisons are required.
  • BaseURL - you may optionally provide a base URL against which all requests are run. This is handy if you don't want your calls to have full URLs in them

Parameters:

execute

public RestCallResult execute(RestCall call)
Executes a rest call. No derived calls are executed. If the http implementation has not been set, this will throw an IllegalStateException.

Parameters:
call - the call to execute.
Returns:
the results of the call. This will always return, no exceptions are thrown from this method

skip

public RestCallResult skip(RestCall call)
Skips the call, generating a result that indicates that. This is preferable to creating RestCallResults yourself as it maintains a consistent means of vending this objects.

Parameters:
call - the call to skip
Returns:
a RestCallResult that indicates that this call was skipped.
